sec.p:
From Equation (13), |Hapf(ejω)|=1, and the unknown coefficients ai(i=1…N) can be calculated from the phase-frequency characteristics. An effective method for designing the coefficients of all-pass filters is described as follows (Reddy and Swamy, 1990):


calculate the time delay sequence without excursion τ(k)=(τd(k)-τ¯d)/2, where τd(k)=τd(ω)|ω=2π/M, M is the length of the fast Fourier transform (FFT) used in the computation, τ¯d=1M∑k=0M-1τd(k);

obtain series p(n) by an inverse FFT (IFFT) of τ(k);

calculate c(n) based on p(n)
c(n)={0n=0,M/2,p(n)/n0<n<M/2,-c(M-n)M/2<n<M.


introduce sign function, where
sgn(n)={0n=0,M/2,1 0<n<M/2,-1M/2<n<M.


calculate the FFT transform of c(n) to obtain series C(k), where C(k) has the phase-frequency characteristics ϕ(k)of the filter we need;

calculate g(n)=sgn(n)·c(n), where 0≤n<M;

calculate the FFT of g(n), and present the result as ln|X(k)|;

calculate D(k)=|X(k)|·ejϕ(k), where k=0,1,…,M-1;

calculate the IFFT transform of D(k), obtaining d(n);

confirm the coefficients of the all-pass filter a(n)=d(n), where n=0,1,…,N(N<M).
